Excellency, apologies. Allow me.


718
0:55:58,769 --> 0:56:0,704
No, no, no. Put it on the table.


719
0:56:0,704 --> 0:56:4,107
The Blutwurst is my favorite dish.


720
0:56:4,107 --> 0:56:5,742
Bring me a knife.


721
0:56:5,742 --> 0:56:10,247
- Come on!
- But why? Why are we going?


722
0:56:10,247 --> 0:56:15,686
You're acting completely like a lunatic!
It was just warming up in there.


723
0:56:15,686 --> 0:56:23,226
Evidently.


724
0:56:23,226 --> 0:56:26,797
- That poor man.
- Archduke Ferdie?


725
0:56:26,797 --> 0:56:30,233
Waste no tears on him.
A petty tyrant, if ever there was one.


726
0:56:30,233 --> 0:56:33,804
An historic event. You should
make an excellent journalist.


727
0:56:33,804 --> 0:56:36,239
You're always on the spot.


728
0:56:36,239 --> 0:56:39,443
- But that bomb was meant for you.
- Precisely.


729
0:56:39,443 --> 0:56:42,446
I thought you said the Bureau
had no one here in Vienna.


730
0:56:42,446 --> 0:56:44,347
They sent someone.


731
0:56:44,347 --> 0:56:51,288
I wonder how they knew I was here.


732
0:56:51,288 --> 0:56:54,524
Perhaps you've been followed.


733
0:56:54,524 --> 0:56:58,628
- Indeed. I have, my dear. By you.
- Me?


734
0:56:58,628 --> 0:57:1,164
At Lord Bostwick's command,
no doubt.


735
0:57:1,164 --> 0:57:3,266
How did you know?
He said not to say...


736
0:57:3,266 --> 0:57:6,403
He also didn't tell you he's
vice chairman of our bureau.


737
0:57:6,403 --> 0:57:9,873
Lord Bostwick?


738
0:57:9,873 --> 0:57:12,809
- I can't believe it.
- A man of many parts.


739
0:57:12,809 --> 0:57:16,58
- He's a villain.
- Well, he'll hear no more from you.


740
0:57:16,58 --> 0:57:20,317
On the contrary. I intend to
keep him fully informed.


741
0:57:20,317 --> 0:57:21,885
You what?


742
0:57:21,885 --> 0:57:25,55
I want to know exactly why
he wants control of the Bureau.


743
0:57:25,55 --> 0:57:30,293
I shall wire him at once
you're on your way to Venice.


744
0:57:30,293 --> 0:57:32,496
Can't you make any more
of it than this?


745
0:57:32,496 --> 0:57:35,899
- There's nothing but facts!
- We mustn't inflame the situation.


746
0:57:35,899 --> 0:57:40,103
Ruthenia and Carpathia are puppets!
Russia and Austria pull the strings.


747
0:57:40,103 --> 0:57:42,372
So punch in some big headlines:


748
0:57:42,372 --> 0:57:46,143
"Russia Warns Austria"!
"Austria Warns Russia"!


749
0:57:46,143 --> 0:57:48,478
"The Kaiser Summons
his General Staff"!


750
0:57:48,478 --> 0:57:50,881
You have private sources
of information?


751
0:57:50,881 --> 0:57:52,883
Of course. So get on with it, man.


752
0:57:52,883 --> 0:57:56,987
We're running a newspaper.
Give them news!


753
0:57:56,987 --> 0:57:59,956
This is a stroke of luck, Muntzov.


754
0:57:59,956 --> 0:58:2,692
Ferdinand's death is the spark
I needed. Cheer up.


755
0:58:2,692 --> 0:58:5,228
To a Russian,
death is a serious matter.


756
0:58:5,228 --> 0:58:8,899
- Life is no joke, either.
- But time is running out.


757
0:58:8,899 --> 0:58:11,1
I've got my new members picked.


758
0:58:11,1 --> 0:58:14,638
But I need the Bureau
in my hands now.


759
0:58:14,638 --> 0:58:18,8
We must make sure once
and for all in Venice.


760
0:58:18,8 --> 0:58:23,18
Thank heaven for Cesare Spado.
He has all the skill of the Borgias.


761
0:58:23,18 --> 0:58:27,784
All my friends in London tell me
I'm getting a little fat.


762
0:58:27,784 --> 0:58:33,59
I can't resist.


763
0:58:33,59 --> 0:58:37,627
My dearest one! You haven't put
vanilla in the zabaglione!


764
0:58:37,627 --> 0:58:41,698
You know how I dislike it!


765
0:58:41,698 --> 0:58:45,202
Nonsense, Cesare.
Just peel of tangerine.


766
0:58:45,202 --> 0:58:49,39
I prepared it myself.
There's not a drop of vanilla in it.


767
0:58:49,39 --> 0:58:51,107
I can taste it distinctly.


768
0:58:51,107 --> 0:58:54,778
There is positively no vanilla
in the zabaglione.


769
0:58:54,778 --> 0:58:59,49
Taste it again.


770
0:58:59,49 --> 0:59:0,55
Perhaps you're right.


771
0:59:0,55 --> 0:59:4,12
Eat it up now or I shall be
very offended.


772
0:59:4,12 --> 0:59:6,923
I will not speak to you.


773
0:59:6,923 --> 0:59:10,26
Or let you...


774
0:59:10,26 --> 0:59:14,998
No, no, no.
Eleanora, my angel...


775
0:59:14,998 --> 0:59:17,67
It's delicious.


776
0:59:17,67 --> 0:59:19,703
I tell everyone your cooking
is supreme.


777
0:59:19,703 --> 0:59:22,572
The taste has quite disappeared.


778
0:59:22,572 --> 0:59:28,678
You've outdone yourself,
my darling.


779
0:59:28,678 --> 0:59:31,815
Eleanora, my dear,
it's just possible that a man


780
0:59:31,815 --> 0:59:34,684
with whom I have business
connections may call here.


781
0:59:34,684 --> 0:59:37,52
- I would prefer not to see him.
- As you wish.


782
0:59:37,52 --> 0:59:41,57
His name is Dragomiloff,
but he may not declare himself.


783
0:59:41,57 --> 0:59:44,261
I would like you to describe carefully
anyone who may call.


784
0:59:44,261 --> 0:59:57,474
What a dreadful fuss.


785
0:59:57,474 --> 0:59:59,209
This is our finest view,


786
0:59:59,209 --> 1:0:2,45
the room Signor Dragomiloff
always prefers, signora.


787
1:0:2,45 --> 1:0:6,82
You will see the sun rise up behind
the Santa Maria della Salute.


788
1:0:6,82 --> 1:0:9,352
- A sight never to be forgotten.
- A little misunderstanding.


789
1:0:9,352 --> 1:0:12,489
I am not a signora and therefore
require a separate room.


790
1:0:12,489 --> 1:0:14,791
Scusi, signorina.
What a pity.


791
1:0:14,791 --> 1:0:17,494
I hope you have another
equally delightful room.


792
1:0:17,494 --> 1:0:19,696
The room, yes, signor.
The view, no.


793
1:0:19,696 --> 1:0:23,166
- I have only a room at the back.
- Then she must have this room.


794
1:0:23,166 --> 1:0:24,668
- Oh, no.
- No, I insist.


795
1:0:24,668 --> 1:0:27,504
Take my luggage to whatever room.
I'll see you later.


796
1:0:27,504 --> 1:0:31,41
It is a very delightful room, signor.
You will be most comfortable.


797
1:0:31,41 --> 1:0:35,578
I'm sure I will.
Thank you very much indeed.


798
1:0:35,578 --> 1:0:38,181
Well, it seems we have
a married look.


799
1:0:38,181 --> 1:0:40,35
Because you're after my blood,
no doubt.


800
1:0:40,35 --> 1:0:45,689
Don't talk nonsense.
We've got no time to waste.


801
1:0:45,689 --> 1:0:48,124
- What are you doing?
- Can't be too careful.


802
1:0:48,124 --> 1:0:54,798
My dear friend Spado might have
left me a welcoming present.


803
1:0:54,798 --> 1:0:57,367
That's all clear.
Bombs aren't the Italian line.


804
1:0:57,367 --> 1:1:1,671
They prefer more subtle methods.


805
1:1:1,671 --> 1:1:5,842
Well, the sooner you talk to him
the better. Isn't it time you left?


806
1:1:5,842 --> 1:1:9,546
Miss Winter.


807
1:1:9,546 --> 1:1:11,781
Since our relationship
became less formal,


808
1:1:11,781 --> 1:1:14,718
I observe a tendency
on your part to nag.


809
1:1:14,718 --> 1:1:19,155
- Sometimes you can be very irritating.
- I have been told that.


810
1:1:19,155 --> 1:1:22,859
Stay here until I return, understand?
Absolutely no one is allowed in.


811
1:1:22,859 --> 1:1:26,62
If you sleep, lock the windows.
The balcony's an easy climb.


812
1:1:26,62 --> 1:1:29,466
To be on the safe side,
I will lock you in and keep the key.


813
1:1:29,466 --> 1:1:32,68
But this is absurd.
If Spado is so dangerous,


814
1:1:32,68 --> 1:1:34,804
how can you hope to win him over
to our plan?


815
1:1:34,804 --> 1:1:37,4
Cesare and my father
were very close.


816
1:1:37,4 --> 1:1:39,42
I doubt he'd go the way
of the others


817
1:1:39,42 --> 1:1:41,745
had it not been
for such a demanding wife.


818
1:1:41,745 --> 1:1:45,582
- As usual, the woman gets the blame.
- Not without good cause, I gather.


819
1:1:45,582 --> 1:1:48,785
I'm told that Signora Spado
has considerable charms


820
1:1:48,785 --> 1:1:53,69
and doesn't hesitate
to use them.


821
1:1:53,69 --> 1:1:55,792
She hasn't your high principles.


822
1:1:55,792 --> 1:1:58,194
Your self-denial is
really quite remarkable.


823
1:1:58,194 --> 1:2:4,534
A woman's beauty
can be a lethal weapon.


824
1:2:4,534 --> 1:2:7,737
- My God.
- My darling, what can it be?


825
1:2:7,737 --> 1:2:10,473
Is it something you have eaten?


826
1:2:10,473 --> 1:2:12,75
It's working.


827
1:2:12,75 --> 1:2:19,616
The poison,
it's doing its work.


828
1:2:19,616 --> 1:2:21,951
Poison?


829
1:2:21,951 --> 1:2:24,687
What are you saying, Cesare?


830
1:2:24,687 --> 1:2:27,624
How could he have managed it?


831
1:2:27,624 --> 1:2:31,294
He? Who are you talking of,
my darling?


832
1:2:31,294 --> 1:2:33,73
The son of my old friend
and comrade.


833
1:2:33,73 --> 1:2:36,8
I had arranged his death,
but he has got me first.


834
1:2:36,8 --> 1:2:40,437
- Cesare, you're delirious.
- There is so much I must tell you.


835
1:2:40,437 --> 1:2:49,746
Lie still.
Angelo has gone for a doctor.


836
1:2:49,746 --> 1:2:51,748
You must hear it all.


837
1:2:51,748 --> 1:2:54,851
This business I am in
with this man Dragomiloff,


838
1:2:54,851 --> 1:3:0,623
it is called...


839
1:3:0,623 --> 1:3:8,398
...the Assassination Bureau.


840
1:3:8,398 --> 1:3:12,335
This Englishman lord
will pay 10,000 pounds


841
1:3:12,335 --> 1:3:14,37
for this man Dragomiloff's death?


842
1:3:14,37 --> 1:3:19,42
Pieces of silver.
Pieces of silver.


843
1:3:19,42 --> 1:3:21,444
Many pieces.


844
1:3:21,444 --> 1:3:24,447
Can you forgive me?


845
1:3:24,447 --> 1:3:29,352
It was for you that I did
these dreadful things.


846
1:3:29,352 --> 1:3:34,23
But you are so tender, so innocent.


847
1:3:34,23 --> 1:4:2,652
What can you know
of assassination?


848
1:4:2,652 --> 1:4:10,693
Life flows along


849
1:4:10,693 --> 1:4:19,302
Just like a boat on a river


850
1:4:19,302 --> 1:4:25,375
All that I want is to


851
1:4:25,375 --> 1:4:29,712
Find a place


852
1:4:29,712 --> 1:4:35,318
Safe in the harbor


853
1:4:35,318 --> 1:4:40,123
Of love's embrace


854
1:4:40,123 --> 1:4:42,792
Good evening.


855
1:4:42,792 --> 1:4:45,795
- Forgive my entering unannounced.
- Who are you?


856
1:4:45,795 --> 1:4:48,798
- A friend of your husband.
- My husband is away.


857
1:4:48,798 --> 1:4:51,1
Strange.


858
1:4:51,1 --> 1:4:53,536
He knew I was coming.


859
1:4:53,536 --> 1:4:56,639
We had some business
to do together.


860
1:4:56,639 --> 1:5:0,81
You... You haven't told me
your name.


861
1:5:0,81 --> 1:5:3,98
My name is...


862
1:5:3,98 --> 1:5:9,18
...lvan Dragomiloff.


863
1:5:9,18 --> 1:5:12,88
Signor Dragomiloff.


864
1:5:12,88 --> 1:5:16,492
I've heard him talk
so often about you.


865
1:5:16,492 --> 1:5:19,462
I feel we are old friends.


866
1:5:19,462 --> 1:5:21,97
Me too.


867
1:5:21,97 --> 1:5:26,469
I have heard much about you.
Cesare is a... A lucky man.


868
1:5:26,469 --> 1:5:30,6
May I ask you
where he has gone?


869
1:5:30,6 --> 1:5:31,441
I don't know.


870
1:5:31,441 --> 1:5:34,344
He's just, well, floating around.


871
1:5:34,344 --> 1:5:37,18
Since you are alone,
my presence might compromise you.


872
1:5:37,18 --> 1:5:41,5
- Perhaps I should go.
- No, no. We'll have a glass of wine.


873
1:5:41,5 --> 1:5:45,521
- Do sit down.
- Thank you.


874
1:5:45,521 --> 1:5:49,325
How much do you know
about his business?


875
1:5:49,325 --> 1:5:51,294
Oh, nothing.


876
1:5:51,294 --> 1:5:56,566
Well, then, you'll hardly be able
to make up for his absence, will you?


877
1:5:56,566 --> 1:6:6,509
I wouldn't say that.


878
1:6:6,509 --> 1:6:8,378
Will you think me
very wicked


879
1:6:8,378 --> 1:6:12,482
if I confess to being pleased
that Cesare is away?


880
1:6:12,482 --> 1:6:14,884
I would think you very flattering.


881
1:6:14,884 --> 1:6:17,754
But that's not the reason
why you made away with him.


882
1:6:17,754 --> 1:6:19,489
I what?!


883
1:6:19,489 --> 1:6:21,924
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to startle you.


884
1:6:21,924 --> 1:6:24,294
How dare you accuse me
of such a thing!


885
1:6:24,294 --> 1:6:25,928
Let's not have melodramatics.


886
1:6:25,928 --> 1:6:28,598
I saw your handsome gondolier
dispose of the body.


887
1:6:28,598 --> 1:6:30,33
Now please sit down.


888
1:6:30,33 --> 1:6:33,836
Perhaps we can come
to some arrangement.


889
1:6:33,836 --> 1:6:42,578
One moment.
Angelo, I must deal with him.


890
1:6:42,578 --> 1:6:44,514
- You have a man in.
- Not for long.


891
1:6:44,514 --> 1:6:47,55
- Long, short, what is the difference?
- Don't be a fool.


892
1:6:47,55 --> 1:6:50,53
He knows. He saw you.
He could destroy us.


893
1:6:50,53 --> 1:6:52,855
- Then I will fix him.
- I will.


894
1:6:52,855 --> 1:6:55,858
My way.


895
1:6:55,858 --> 1:6:58,27
Go and prepare the gondola,
then wait.


896
1:6:58,27 --> 1:7:6,102
I will ring when it is done.
It will be quick this time.


897
1:7:6,102 --> 1:7:9,205
You can't prove
your ridiculous accusation.


898
1:7:9,205 --> 1:7:10,773
I hope I won't have to.


899
1:7:10,773 --> 1:7:12,875
We have plenty of time
to talk it over.


900
1:7:12,875 --> 1:7:16,179
Then let's have
another glass of wine.


901
1:7:16,179 --> 1:7:20,717
Please, close the window.
The night has grown chilly.


902
1:7:20,717 --> 1:7:22,752
Even if what you say was true,


903
1:7:22,752 --> 1:7:29,192
wouldn't I have been merely doing
your job for you?


904
1:7:29,192 --> 1:7:32,28
You said you knew nothing
of your husband's business.


905
1:7:32,28 --> 1:7:43,206
Perhaps it is now my business.


906
1:7:43,206 --> 1:7:46,242
I'm sure that you'll handle it
very capably.


907
1:7:46,242 --> 1:7:51,814
Thank you.


908
1:7:51,814 --> 1:8:0,323
Please draw the curtains.


909
1:8:0,323 --> 1:8:2,725
It appears we understand
each other well.


910
1:8:2,725 --> 1:8:5,461
- Sit down, please.
- Thank you.


911
1:8:5,461 --> 1:8:8,331
I told you I could take
my husband's place.


912
1:8:8,331 --> 1:8:13,236
What a delightful little table,
like a wheel of fortune.


913
1:8:13,236 --> 1:8:15,37
Our fortunes, it seems,


914
1:8:15,37 --> 1:8:16,572
are to be linked.


915
1:8:16,572 --> 1:8:19,509
- Shall we drink to that?
- I...


916
1:8:19,509 --> 1:8:23,479
- I can't drink to the unknown.
- You're not adventurous.


917
1:8:23,479 --> 1:8:49,672
I drink to it.


918
1:8:49,672 --> 1:8:53,543
Bellissima.


919
1:8:53,543 --> 1:8:55,578
Get rid of him.


920
1:8:55,578 --> 1:8:57,38
What a pity.


921
1:8:57,38 --> 1:9:0,65
He was so young.


922
1:9:0,65 --> 1:9:5,555
All that I want is to


923
1:9:5,555 --> 1:9:9,559
Find a place


924
1:9:9,559 --> 1:9:14,53
Safe in the harbor


925
1:9:14,53 --> 1:9:18,401
Of love's embrace


926
1:9:18,401 --> 1:12:38,834
How sweet...


927
1:12:38,834 --> 1:12:40,87
Fortunately, I kept wicket for Eton.


928
1:12:40,87 --> 1:12:44,473
- Oh, don't worry, I've turned it off.
- It...


929
1:12:44,473 --> 1:12:46,809
It was on the canopy.


930
1:12:46,809 --> 1:12:50,279
Splendid. I knew these new
time bombs would come in useful.


931
1:12:50,279 --> 1:12:55,51
Can't you talk anything but shop?
I've nearly been killed.


932
1:12:55,51 --> 1:12:58,32
Oh, I'm sorry.


933
1:12:58,32 --> 1:13:3,259
I am sorry.


934
1:13:3,259 --> 1:13:5,261
I'll never forgive myself.


935
1:13:5,261 --> 1:13:12,201
This room was meant for me.
I should never have left you here.


936
1:13:12,201 --> 1:13:16,305
What on earth are you doing
in that ridiculous costume?


937
1:13:16,305 --> 1:13:18,107
I forgot.


938
1:13:18,107 --> 1:13:23,779
I regret to have to inform you
that lvan Dragomiloff is now dead.


939
1:13:23,779 --> 1:13:26,749
- What?
- Yes, events took an unexpected turn.


940
1:13:26,749 --> 1:13:29,652
However, the first part of our plot
has been achieved.


941
1:13:29,652 --> 1:13:32,154
- You mean they think you're dead?
- Precisely.


942
1:13:32,154 --> 1:13:35,91
I shall now have to disappear
into hiding.


943
1:13:35,91 --> 1:13:40,663
And the rest, Miss Winter,
is up to you.


944
1:13:40,663 --> 1:13:59,381
Now, that's what I call
a really pretty dress.


945
1:13:59,381 --> 1:14:10,259
Miss Winter.


946
1:14:10,259 --> 1:14:20,35
Miss Winter, surrender.


947
1:14:20,35 --> 1:14:22,37
Why not?


948
1:14:22,37 --> 1:14:24,54
Surrender is no defeat...


949
1:14:24,54 --> 1:14:39,188
...for a woman.


950
1:14:39,188 --> 1:14:42,892
My friend has not returned to the hotel.
He's been out all night.


951
1:14:42,892 --> 1:14:45,694
I'm desperately afraid
he was run over.


952
1:14:45,694 --> 1:14:49,799
- In Venice, signorina?
- Well, fallen in a canal, anything.


953
1:14:49,799 --> 1:14:52,568
- Please, you must help me.
- Of course, signorina.


954
1:14:52,568 --> 1:14:55,271
- The name of your friend?
- Dragomiloff.


955
1:14:55,271 --> 1:14:57,306
Ivan Dragomiloff.


956
1:14:57,306 --> 1:15:11,487
One moment, signorina.


957
1:15:11,487 --> 1:15:14,89
Signorina, I am sorry.


958
1:15:14,89 --> 1:15:18,194
- I fear I have very bad news.
- What?


959
1:15:18,194 --> 1:15:20,129
- What is it?
- Your friend.


960
1:15:20,129 --> 1:15:23,365
There must have been an accident.
He has been drowned.


961
1:15:23,365 --> 1:15:32,274
His body has been taken
from the canal.


962
1:15:32,274 --> 1:15:35,711
- I'll be all right.
- There were papers with his name.


963
1:15:35,711 --> 1:15:44,887
But we would like you to identify
the body, if you are able.


964
1:15:44,887 --> 1:16:12,915
- Very well.
- Please come this way, signorina.


965
1:16:12,915 --> 1:16:15,15
It is...


966
1:16:15,15 --> 1:16:22,391
...he.


967
1:16:22,391 --> 1:16:40,743
This way, signorina.


968
1:16:40,743 --> 1:16:44,113
It... It... It is him.


969
1:16:44,113 --> 1:16:48,25
- Yes, we found papers on the body.
- Was Dragomiloff a good friend?


970
1:16:48,25 --> 1:16:51,186
He was the best friend
my husband had.


971
1:16:51,186 --> 1:16:53,122
We were very close.


972
1:16:53,122 --> 1:16:56,625
We will save you
any more pain, signora.


973
1:16:56,625 --> 1:17:0,95
I would be very glad if he could
be brought to my palazzo.


974
1:17:0,95 --> 1:17:5,434
It is not fitting that such a man
should lie here.


975
1:17:5,434 --> 1:17:7,87
Whatever the signora desires.


976
1:17:7,87 --> 1:17:9,838
We salvaged the gondola, signora.


977
1:17:9,838 --> 1:17:13,876
But alas, there is as yet
no sign of the gondolier.


978
1:17:13,876 --> 1:18:4,994
Poor Angelo.


979
1:18:4,994 --> 1:18:8,197
Poor Angelo's clothes
fit you perfectly.


980
1:18:8,197 --> 1:18:12,134
A little tight, perhaps,
because you are more muscular.


981
1:18:12,134 --> 1:18:14,37
I prefer that.


982
1:18:14,37 --> 1:18:16,205
Go to the undertakers.


983
1:18:16,205 --> 1:18:18,707
I want this gruesome thing removed


984
1:18:18,707 --> 1:18:21,71
as soon as my guests
have paid their respects.


985
1:18:21,71 --> 1:18:26,448
Well, come along, Piero.
Get on with it.


986
1:18:26,448 --> 1:18:43,599
I hope you're not going
to take liberties.


987
1:18:43,599 --> 1:18:48,27
Miss Winter?


988
1:18:48,27 --> 1:18:50,973
Miss Winter,
I hardly recognized you.


989
1:18:50,973 --> 1:18:53,275
- My congratulations.
- Lord Bostwick.


990
1:18:53,275 --> 1:18:56,845
I came as soon as I received
your telegram announcing his death.


991
1:18:56,845 --> 1:18:59,648
May I introduce an associate of mine,
Baron Muntzov.


992
1:18:59,648 --> 1:19:1,25
Well, my dear young lady,


993
1:19:1,25 --> 1:19:5,154
the press has once again shown itself
to be the conscience of the nation.


994
1:19:5,154 --> 1:19:8,9
Your story will be syndicated
all over the world.


995
1:19:8,9 --> 1:19:10,392
Come, we will go directly
to Spado's house,


996
1:19:10,392 --> 1:19:12,694
and pay our respects
to the dead.


997
1:19:12,694 --> 1:19:14,129
At Spado's house?


998
1:19:14,129 --> 1:19:15,931
But his body is at the morgue.


999
1:19:15,931 --> 1:19:20,369
As I so often find, my information
is more up-to-date than my reporters'.


1000
1:19:20,369 --> 1:19:23,539
Signora Spado's had the coffin
taken to her palazzo.


1001
1:19:23,539 --> 1:19:26,475
My lord. My lord.


1002
1:19:26,475 --> 1:19:30,913
I've just arrived from Berlin,
the news is grave.


1003
1:19:30,913 --> 1:19:35,15
Dragomiloff has gone
just in time.


1004
1:19:35,15 --> 1:19:38,287
Miss Winter, may I introduce
General von Pinck.


1005
1:19:38,287 --> 1:19:40,722
Collect the luggage
and bring Miss Winter.


1006
1:19:40,722 --> 1:19:48,63
The general and I will go on ahead.
We have important matters to discuss.


1007
1:19:48,63 --> 1:19:55,571
There's mobilization.
I must return tonight.


1008
1:19:55,571 --> 1:19:57,206
Will there be war?


1009
1:19:57,206 --> 1:20:0,309
Not yet, the kaiser's proposing
a secret peace conference.


1010
1:20:0,309 --> 1:20:3,479
- Indeed.
- He goes to Ruthenia for the funeral,


1011
1:20:3,479 --> 1:20:6,215
and that's where
the conference will take place.


1012
1:20:6,215 --> 1:20:10,252
They will all be there:
The English king. Tsar Nicholas.


1013
1:20:10,252 --> 1:20:13,322
The president of France.
The Austrian emperor. The...


1014
1:20:13,322 --> 1:20:16,458
Spare me this catalog
of mediocrity.


1015
1:20:16,458 --> 1:20:25,2
All this may suit me very well.


1016
1:20:25,2 --> 1:20:27,903
Signora Spado, my greetings
and congratulations.


1017
1:20:27,903 --> 1:20:30,272
My colleague, General von Pinck.


1018
1:20:30,272 --> 1:20:32,975
My husband is away.
I had to act on his behalf.


1019
1:20:32,975 --> 1:20:37,179
It's hard to believe a beautiful lady
succeeds where many men failed.


1020
1:20:37,179 --> 1:20:39,248
We should invite you
onto the board.


1021
1:20:39,248 --> 1:20:42,417
Thank you, Lord Bostwick.
But I don't think it is suitable


1022
1:20:42,417 --> 1:20:45,954
for an Italian lady to
practice murder professionally.


1023
1:20:45,954 --> 1:20:49,691
I will be content with the reward
you have so kindly offered.


1024
1:20:49,691 --> 1:20:52,461
And you shall have it, dear lady.


1025
1:20:52,461 --> 1:20:54,53
So there he lies.


1026
1:20:54,53 --> 1:20:56,31
Poor lvan.


1027
1:20:56,31 --> 1:20:59,468
He was too young to see
the potentialities of his inheritance.


1028
1:20:59,468 --> 1:21:1,36
Requiescat in pace.


1029
1:21:1,36 --> 1:21:4,54
Ivan killed by a woman, that's droll.


1030
1:21:4,54 --> 1:21:7,709
I believe Spado's house
is quite beautiful.


1031
1:21:7,709 --> 1:21:11,346
As with so many things,
first impressions are the worst.


1032
1:21:11,346 --> 1:21:14,95
This way, signorina.


1033
1:21:14,95 --> 1:21:16,985
And so you see,
my dear signora,


1034
1:21:16,985 --> 1:21:22,391
this young lady has served
her purpose and must be disposed of.


1035
1:21:22,391 --> 1:21:25,794
Miss Winter, Muntzov has been
monopolizing you.


1036
1:21:25,794 --> 1:21:27,996
Signora Spado, this is Miss Winter,


1037
1:21:27,996 --> 1:21:34,403
whose commission you executed
on behalf of your husband.


1038
1:21:34,403 --> 1:21:38,4
If you'll excuse me, I'll make a room
ready for the discussion.


1039
1:21:38,4 --> 1:21:40,409
No, no, no.
This will do splendidly.


1040
1:21:40,409 --> 1:21:44,12
The presence of our ex-chairman
will be a spur to our deliberations.


1041
1:21:44,12 --> 1:21:46,815
You openly admit you are a member
of the Bureau?


1042
1:21:46,815 --> 1:21:48,25
A member?


1043
1:21:48,25 --> 1:21:51,22
Thanks to you and Signora Spado,
I am now the chairman.


1044
1:21:51,22 --> 1:21:53,355
What a journalist
you would have made.


1045
1:21:53,355 --> 1:21:56,491
In at the death of the old Bureau
and the birth of the new.


1046
1:21:56,491 --> 1:22:7,169
Unfortunately, you must also be
its first victim.


1047
1:22:7,169 --> 1:22:10,372
Dispose of her, Muntzov.
It's time you did something useful.


1048
1:22:10,372 --> 1:22:18,647
This way.


1049
1:22:18,647 --> 1:22:21,49
Take her below.
There are steps to the canal.


1050
1:22:21,49 --> 1:22:37,666
Don't make any false moves.
I'm a dangerous man.


1051
1:22:37,666 --> 1:22:45,707
Go to that wall, please,
Miss Winter.


1052
1:22:45,707 --> 1:22:48,377
If you would please face
the wall, my dear.


1053
1:22:48,377 --> 1:22:50,912
We Slavs are so temperamental.


1054
1:22:50,912 --> 1:22:54,383
Somehow, I don't feel like it
at all today.


1055
1:22:54,383 --> 1:22:57,152
So you're a coward as well
as a murderer.


1056
1:22:57,152 --> 1:23:1,323
I don't seem really to care
for killing people anymore.


1057
1:23:1,323 --> 1:23:4,793
Keep quite still, Miss Winter.


1058
1:23:4,793 --> 1:23:44,733
It's best to make a clean job of it.


1059
1:23:44,733 --> 1:23:49,338
Ivan.


1060
1:23:49,338 --> 1:23:51,573
What on earth?


1061
1:23:51,573 --> 1:23:55,11
- I'm in mourning.
- For your lost principles, I presume?


1062
1:23:55,11 --> 1:23:57,879
You look like you're got up
to seduce an archbishop.


1063
1:23:57,879 --> 1:24:1,65
- Don't you like it?
- Oh, I'm turning in my grave.


1064
1:24:1,65 --> 1:24:6,221
Will you at least get rid
of that preposterous hat.


1065
1:24:6,221 --> 1:24:9,891
- How dare you!
- That's better.


1066
1:24:9,891 --> 1:24:12,327
At any rate, you played
your part admirably.


1067
1:24:12,327 --> 1:24:14,963
See what results the report
of my death produced.


1068
1:24:14,963 --> 1:24:18,2
- It nearly produced mine.
- It's brought them here,


1069
1:24:18,2 --> 1:24:19,768
as I knew it would.


1070
1:24:19,768 --> 1:24:22,704
Now we see whether
I can learn more dead than alive.


1071
1:24:22,704 --> 1:24:25,307
But the coffin in the room upstairs,
who's in it?


1072
1:24:25,307 --> 1:24:28,61
The man you identified as me,
of course, her gondolier.


1073
1:24:28,61 --> 1:24:30,946
- Muntzov!
- Come on.


1074
1:24:30,946 --> 1:24:32,414
Muntzov, where are you?


1075
1:24:32,414 --> 1:24:34,95
- Where could that idiot go?
- He'd be here.


1076
1:24:34,95 --> 1:24:38,286
The secret stairs from my apartments
lead down to that landing.


1077
1:24:38,286 --> 1:24:41,923
A girl, even Muntzov
couldn't fail.


1078
1:24:41,923 --> 1:24:44,326
He evidently did.


1079
1:24:44,326 --> 1:24:46,661
And the girl's hat.


1080
1:24:46,661 --> 1:24:53,969
- If he killed her, then...
- Then who killed him?


1081
1:24:53,969 --> 1:24:57,272
- I want to see inside that coffin.
- Oh, no.


1082
1:24:57,272 --> 1:25:11,686
- And why not, signora?
- You're not squeamish, surely?


1083
1:25:11,686 --> 1:25:13,655
Take off the lid.


1084
1:25:13,655 --> 1:25:34,9
- Please, don't disturb the dead.
- Be silent.


1085
1:25:34,9 --> 1:25:41,183
Replace the lid.


1086
1:25:41,183 --> 1:25:44,686
My apologies, signora.
You've done your job well.


1087
1:25:44,686 --> 1:25:50,892
Don't worry, signora.
He can't get away.


1088
1:25:50,892 --> 1:25:54,796
General, I will return to Germany.
Where will your headquarters be?


1089
1:25:54,796 --> 1:25:57,132
At my hunting lodge at Rothenburg.


1090
1:25:57,132 --> 1:26:2,17
The peace conference will take place
across the frontier in the Castle Minsk.


1091
1:26:2,17 --> 1:26:6,41
Convenient. I'll summon the Bureau
members to meet us at Rothenburg.


1092
1:26:6,41 --> 1:26:11,413
- But my staff will be there, officers.
- Of course, and they'll be very useful.


1093
1:26:11,413 --> 1:26:13,648
So goodbye, lvan.


1094
1:26:13,648 --> 1:26:17,85
You're going to miss
our greatest assignment of all.


1095
1:26:17,85 --> 1:26:24,96
At my commission,
the assassination of Europe.


1096
1:26:24,96 --> 1:26:29,297
They have come to take him away.


1097
1:26:29,297 --> 1:27:55,15
Make sure the screws are tight.


1098
1:27:55,15 --> 1:27:59,487
We'll have a glass of wine, and then
we can complete our business.


1099
1:27:59,487 --> 1:28:1,756
Of course, the reward.


1100
1:28:1,756 --> 1:28:4,459
I suppose it was rather tactless
of Cesare


1101
1:28:4,459 --> 1:28:7,128
to tell me so much about
your secret business.


1102
1:28:7,128 --> 1:28:10,465
Who can quarrel with
such an excellent result?


1103
1:28:10,465 --> 1:28:13,401
Surely it is worth more
than a mere 10,000 pounds?


1104
1:28:13,401 --> 1:28:15,537
Of course.
How much would you suggest?


1105
1:28:15,537 --> 1:28:19,7
Naturally, you would not like
your affairs made public.


1106
1:28:19,7 --> 1:28:22,444
Shall we say 100,000?


1107
1:28:22,444 --> 1:28:25,347
Oh, alas, signora,
we are not a rich organization.


1108
1:28:25,347 --> 1:28:29,584
But you have such great plans
now that I have given you control.


1109
1:28:29,584 --> 1:28:32,654
Surely that is worth
special consideration?


1110
1:28:32,654 --> 1:28:34,122
Indeed.


1111
1:28:34,122 --> 1:29:9,624
Von Pinck, see that signora gets the
most special consideration we offer.


1112
1:29:9,624 --> 1:29:23,605
Well done, Miss Winter.
On the spot as usual.


1113
1:29:23,605 --> 1:29:28,109
As Europe's heads of state travel
to Ruthenia for the funeral of its ruler,


1114
1:29:28,109 --> 1:29:33,515
the Archduke Ferdinand's tragic death
threatens to set Europe ablaze.


1115
1:29:33,515 --> 1:29:36,685
Throughout Germany
and the Austro-Hungarian Empire,


1116
1:29:36,685 --> 1:29:41,89
troops of the Grand Alliance are
moving toward the Ruthenian frontier.


1117
1:29:41,89 --> 1:29:45,26
In Russia, Tsar Nicholas assumes
personal command of his forces,


1118
1:29:45,26 --> 1:29:48,797
as his Balkan allies call impatiently
for action.


1119
1:29:48,797 --> 1:29:52,767
In the Republic of France, military
preparations are already afoot.


1120
1:29:52,767 --> 1:30:3,645
Great Britain puts her armed forces
in a state of instant readiness.


1121
1:30:3,645 --> 1:30:8,216
After the funeral, the heads of state
will proceed to the royal castle at Minsk.


1122
1:30:8,216 --> 1:30:11,586
Here, close to the Ruthenian border
with Germany.


1123
1:30:11,586 --> 1:30:15,724
Just across the valley at Rothenburg
is a German army...


1124
1:30:15,724 --> 1:30:18,793
...commanded by
General von Pinck.


1125
1:30:18,793 --> 1:30:21,93
- What do you make of it?
- The kaiser is at the conference.


1126
1:30:21,93 --> 1:30:24,966
- What can the German army do?
- Nothing.


1127
1:30:24,966 --> 1:30:30,672
But what Lord Bostwick does with the
remains of my bureau is the question.


1128
1:30:30,672 --> 1:30:32,307
Mein Gott!


1129
1:30:32,307 --> 1:30:35,944
You might look all right
around the board table, my friends,


1130
1:30:35,944 --> 1:30:39,681
but thank God
I don't have to take you into battle.


1131
1:30:39,681 --> 1:30:49,357
That goes under the jacket, man.


1132
1:30:49,357 --> 1:30:51,292
The Russian anthem.


1133
1:30:51,292 --> 1:30:53,428
The czar is arriving.


1134
1:30:53,428 --> 1:30:56,64
We shall need an anthem
of our own.


1135
1:30:56,64 --> 1:30:58,366
Remind me.


1136
1:30:58,366 --> 1:31:20,54
The czar.


1137
1:31:20,54 --> 1:31:23,458
The others will soon be here.


1138
1:31:23,458 --> 1:31:26,561
The time has come to
make a move, gentlemen.


1139
1:31:26,561 --> 1:31:28,93
Are your officers
safely under lock and key?


1140
1:31:28,93 --> 1:31:31,466
Quite safe and very angry
in their underwear.


1141
1:31:31,466 --> 1:31:35,103
I've sent a limber ahead
with our little toy.


1142
1:31:35,103 --> 1:31:43,912
My engineers will have it loaded
by the time we arrive.


1143
1:31:43,912 --> 1:31:46,648
There it is,
the castle at Minsk.


1144
1:31:46,648 --> 1:31:50,518
All the crowned heads of Europe
under one roof, what an opportunity.


1145
1:31:50,518 --> 1:31:52,2
Now, lvan.


1146
1:31:52,2 --> 1:31:54,689
For his lordship, I mean,
if war is what he wants.


1147
1:31:54,689 --> 1:31:58,126
With your ideas, I'm surprised
you're shocked at war.


1148
1:31:58,126 --> 1:32:1,863
Not at all. It's a matter of business.
How can we charge our prices


1149
1:32:1,863 --> 1:32:5,4
with everybody happily killing
each other for a shilling a day?


1150
1:32:5,4 --> 1:32:30,758
Look out.


1151
1:32:30,758 --> 1:32:32,393
- What is it?
- A bomb.


1152
1:32:32,393 --> 1:32:34,162
It's so big.
What will they do?


1153
1:32:34,162 --> 1:32:35,597
- Drop it.
- What?


1154
1:32:35,597 --> 1:32:38,9
On the castle. Ride there quickly.
It must be evacuated.


1155
1:32:38,9 --> 1:32:51,412
- But the frontier will be guarded.
- Ride, I say. I must follow that bomb.


1156
1:32:51,412 --> 1:34:3,551
French president.


1157
1:34:3,551 --> 1:34:5,219
Vorsicht, vorsicht.


1158
1:34:5,219 --> 1:34:8,623
Corporal? Corporal!


1159
1:34:8,623 --> 1:34:10,858
What are you doing?
What is that thing?


1160
1:34:10,858 --> 1:34:13,261
Some new sort of bomb.
We are to load it.


1161
1:34:13,261 --> 1:34:15,83
Aboard my zeppelin?
What's the devil next?


1162
1:34:15,83 --> 1:34:18,666
- General's orders, sir.
- This is a naval ship.


1163
1:34:18,666 --> 1:34:23,738
We'll soon see about that.


1164
1:34:23,738 --> 1:34:26,507
Come on, come on, get busy, there.


1165
1:34:26,507 --> 1:34:28,476
Los, get this thing unloaded.


1166
1:34:28,476 --> 1:34:31,379
The general gave me
the order himself. Los!


1167
1:34:31,379 --> 1:34:35,216
What the devil are you talking about?
Bombs in zeppelins, ridiculous.


1168
1:34:35,216 --> 1:34:45,893
Weg mit dem Objekt. Es muss
heute nicht getan werden.


1169
1:34:45,893 --> 1:35:2,81
Get up.


1170
1:35:2,81 --> 1:35:6,481
A life on the ocean wave and here
we are in the middle of a forest


1171
1:35:6,481 --> 1:35:9,65
- with a bloody gas bag.
- You men there,


1172
1:35:9,65 --> 1:35:12,86
what are you doing?
Do up your buttons.


1173
1:35:12,86 --> 1:35:13,721
Where is your officer?


1174
1:35:13,721 --> 1:35:16,724
- Your officer, where is he?
- He was here a moment ago.


1175
1:35:16,724 --> 1:35:19,494
Well, he is not here now.
I shall take over command.


1176
1:35:19,494 --> 1:35:21,662
General's orders.
The zeppelin takes off


1177
1:35:21,662 --> 1:35:25,7
and returns to base immediately.
Get that thing away from there.


1178
1:35:25,7 --> 1:35:28,669
Corporal, do you hear me?
Get that thing away from here!


1179
1:35:28,669 --> 1:35:31,339
Jawohl, Herr Kapitan.


1180
1:35:31,339 --> 1:35:32,94
Bloody officers.


1181
1:35:32,94 --> 1:35:36,511
- Who is the pilot?
- The Herr Kapitan, Herr Kapitan.


1182
1:35:36,511 --> 1:35:40,348
- But he is not here.
- Well, I also am a pilot, Herr Kapitan.


1183
1:35:40,348 --> 1:35:46,254
Then why didn't you say so?
Get on with it, man.


1184
1:35:46,254 --> 1:35:49,29
Get that thing down here.


1185
1:35:49,29 --> 1:36:16,384
Careful, careful.


1186
1:36:16,384 --> 1:36:19,954
- Hey, you. Where's the officer?
- Well, there was one here.


1187
1:36:19,954 --> 1:36:22,69
- Where is he now?
- I don't know, Herr General.


1188
1:36:22,69 --> 1:36:25,159
- We've lost one already.
- Don't answer back.


1189
1:36:25,159 --> 1:36:28,429
Prepare to take off immediately.


1190
1:36:28,429 --> 1:36:30,364
What are you doing there, corporal?


1191
1:36:30,364 --> 1:36:52,887
- Get that thing aboard.
- Jawohl, Herr General.


1192
1:36:52,887 --> 1:36:55,49
- Where are you going?
- I must go to the castle.


1193
1:36:55,49 --> 1:36:59,227
You have, have you? The frontier
is closed. No one is allowed through.


1194
1:36:59,227 --> 1:37:2,23
The castle must be evacuated.
They're gonna bomb it.


1195
1:37:2,23 --> 1:37:6,267
Do you think we're idiots in Ruthenia?
Evacuate! They've only just arrived.


1196
1:37:6,267 --> 1:37:8,636
They are going
to drop a bomb, I tell you.


1197
1:37:8,636 --> 1:37:15,877
Oh, drop it?
Who is going to? An eagle?


1198
1:37:15,877 --> 1:37:17,812
Through you go.


1199
1:37:17,812 --> 1:37:23,651
There are no frontiers
for the Sisters of Mercy.


1200
1:37:23,651 --> 1:37:25,686
Will you please listen to me?


1201
1:37:25,686 --> 1:37:36,597
Get out of here,
before I have you arrested.


1202
1:37:36,597 --> 1:37:38,9
Heave ho.


1203
1:37:38,9 --> 1:37:41,369
Heave.


1204
1:37:41,369 --> 1:37:43,905
Heave.


1205
1:37:43,905 --> 1:37:46,807
Heave ho.


1206
1:37:46,807 --> 1:37:50,645
Steady. Good.


1207
1:37:50,645 --> 1:37:52,413
Up.


1208
1:37:52,413 --> 1:37:55,55
- Up. Up.
- Careful.


1209
1:37:55,55 --> 1:37:58,719
Up. Up.


1210
1:37:58,719 --> 1:38:3,124
Halt.


1211
1:38:3,124 --> 1:38:11,966
The bomb is secured.


1212
1:38:11,966 --> 1:38:28,983
Stand by to cast off.


1213
1:38:28,983 --> 1:38:33,955
Release ballast.


1214
1:38:33,955 --> 1:38:37,191
Cast off of it.


1215
1:38:37,191 --> 1:38:48,769
Cast off now.


1216
1:38:48,769 --> 1:38:51,973
- Set course for Minsk.
- Minsk, Herr General?


1217
1:38:51,973 --> 1:39:14,595
Drive and ask no questions.


1218
1:39:14,595 --> 1:39:18,266
Bombs from the air.
What a marvelous idea.


1219
1:39:18,266 --> 1:39:28,75
All those little houses down there, just
pull a lever and poof! They're gone.


1220
1:39:28,75 --> 1:39:45,59
My God, let's go and see.


1221
1:39:45,59 --> 1:39:58,606
Dragomiloff!


1222
1:39:58,606 --> 1:40:2,743
Revolutionary idea, general,
an aerial bomb.


1223
1:40:2,743 --> 1:40:10,51
History in the making.
A frightening concept.


1224
1:40:10,51 --> 1:40:42,49
In 15 minutes,
we should be over the castle.


1225
1:40:42,49 --> 1:40:57,31
What's that fool up to?


1226
1:40:57,31 --> 1:41:51,318
- What the devil are you doing there?
- There's a naval officer onboard.


1227
1:41:51,318 --> 1:41:55,956
Get it back on course.


1228
1:41:55,956 --> 1:41:58,559
The captain. He must
have hidden on board.


1229
1:41:58,559 --> 1:42:5,166
- Well, why didn't you search?
- He'll give no more trouble.


1230
1:42:5,166 --> 1:42:7,334
- We're back on course.
- Not too soon.


1231
1:42:7,334 --> 1:42:16,844
We're approaching the frontier.


1232
1:42:16,844 --> 1:42:19,346
Look! Look!


1233
1:42:19,346 --> 1:42:21,382
So, what is this?


1234
1:42:21,382 --> 1:42:26,554
It is un ballon.


1235
1:42:26,554 --> 1:42:32,226
By Jove! It looks like
some sort of airship.


1236
1:42:32,226 --> 1:42:34,762
Nothing is supposed
to cross the frontier.


1237
1:42:34,762 --> 1:42:37,598
It's one of those damned zeppelins.
Where's that Hun?


1238
1:42:37,598 --> 1:42:40,601
- Good morning.
- There you are, Herr Oberleutnant.


1239
1:42:40,601 --> 1:42:42,369
General von Pinck has sent word.


1240
1:42:42,369 --> 1:42:46,106
- It's a patrol for security purposes.
- Why was I not informed?


1241
1:42:46,106 --> 1:42:49,477
- Prussians do what they like.
- They're invading our frontier.


1242
1:42:49,477 --> 1:42:51,779
Now, then. Now, then.
Steady the butts.


1243
1:42:51,779 --> 1:43:3,958
This is supposed to be
a peace conference.


1244
1:43:3,958 --> 1:43:12,766
- Starboard two points.
- Gentlemen.


1245
1:43:12,766 --> 1:43:14,969
Dragomiloff.


1246
1:43:14,969 --> 1:43:18,38
- It's impossible.
- Nothing's impossible, general.


1247
1:43:18,38 --> 1:43:21,408
- This time we'll make quite sure.
- Unwise, my lord.


1248
1:43:21,408 --> 1:43:27,181
You see, a bullet through a hydrogen
balloon will blow us all out of the sky.


1249
1:43:27,181 --> 1:43:29,617
It's true, my lord.
Leave him to me.


1250
1:43:29,617 --> 1:43:32,553
He will not stand a chance.


1251
1:43:32,553 --> 1:43:42,496
I was the saber champion
of all Germany.


1252
1:43:42,496 --> 1:43:59,446
En garde.


1253
1:43:59,446 --> 1:44:3,25
Now, here! And here!


1254
1:44:3,25 --> 1:44:5,386
Come on.


1255
1:44:5,386 --> 1:44:7,221
Very good.


1256
1:44:7,221 --> 1:44:17,298
Take this.


1257
1:44:17,298 --> 1:44:49,496
Here, here, here.


1258
1:44:49,496 --> 1:44:57,905
- Get him.
- This way. After him.


1259
1:44:57,905 --> 1:45:1,542
Keep her steady.


1260
1:45:1,542 --> 1:45:5,679
Don't do it, Charles. Indiscriminate
destruction will engulf you too.


1261
1:45:5,679 --> 1:45:8,349
One death or a million,
where's the difference?


1262
1:45:8,349 --> 1:45:11,852
We're surgeons, not butchers.
We only kill to destroy evil.


1263
1:45:11,852 --> 1:45:15,99
- Hypocrite. You kill for money.
- Only those who deserve to die.


1264
1:45:15,99 --> 1:45:19,526
- We must judge before we kill.
- Judge? Young fool.


1265
1:45:19,526 --> 1:45:22,496
You're not an assassin,
you're a critic.


1266
1:45:22,496 --> 1:45:25,65
Steady.


1267
1:45:25,65 --> 1:46:1,201
Steady.


1268
1:46:1,201 --> 1:47:48,108
It's jammed.


1269
1:47:48,108 --> 1:47:52,112
Damn you, get out of my way.


1270
1:47:52,112 --> 1:47:58,485
Rise, Sir lvan.


1271
1:47:58,485 --> 1:48:3,49
Your Majesties, you must evacuate
the castle immediately.


1272
1:48:3,49 --> 1:48:6,827
Miss Winter, not quite
on the spot for once.


1273
1:48:6,827 --> 1:48:11,198
- Ivan, what happened?
- Sir lvan, if you please.


1274
1:48:11,198 --> 1:48:13,867
Virtue has been rewarded.


1275
1:48:13,867 --> 1:50:13,867
Well, really.


